🎯 Task 4 — Object Detection & Tracking (**TITAN**)
📌 What is this?


**TITAN** stands for:


Tracking & Identification Technology for Autonomous Networks


It is a real-time AI application capable of:


Detecting objects from webcam/video Tracking moving objects Detecting hands and body pose Drawing full body skeletons Assigning tracking IDs to objects ⚙️ How It Works


**TITAN** uses three AI engines simultaneously.


🧠 Engine 1 — YOLOv8 (Object Detection)


YOLOv8 detects:


Person Phone Laptop Chair Bottle Car Dog 70+ more object classes Features Bounding boxes Confidence score Real-time detection Persistent object IDs using ByteTrack 🧠 Engine 2 — MediaPipe Pose


Detects:


Full body skeleton 33 body landmarks Hands Legs Arms Ankles Knees 🧠 Engine 3 — MediaPipe Hands


Detects:


Left and right hand separately
21 finger landmarks per hand
Detailed finger movement tracking
✨ Features
🎯 80 **COCO** object classes
🦴 Full-body skeleton tracking
✋ Hand landmark detection
👣 Leg tracking
📈 Motion trails
📊 **FPS** monitoring
🖥 **HUD** overlay
🔲 Rule-of-thirds grid
⌨ Keyboard Controls
Key Action
P   Pause / Resume
Q   Quit
G   Toggle Grid
T   Toggle Motion Trails
S   Toggle Skeleton
🛠 Technologies Used
Technology  Purpose
Python  Core programming
YOLOv8  Object detection
ByteTrack   Object tracking
MediaPipe   Pose & hand tracking
OpenCV  Video processing
